12 v:shapes=3D"Picture_x0020_0"><![endif]><span
lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>Exploration Ships are purpos=
e-built:
they are fast and have powerful resource profile sensors that allow them to
scan for resources at planets and moons.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>Y=
ou can
manually assign exploration missions to your exploration ships, or you can
automate them so that they seek out unexplored areas on their own.<o:p></o:=
p></span></p>

<h3><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>System Visibility<=
o:p></o:p></span></h3>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>B=
efore your
empire&#8217;s first visit to a system, it is unexplored. You cannot see any
planets or moons in the system.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>W=
hen you
visit the system for the first time it then becomes explored &#8211; you can
then always see all the planets and moons in the system.<o:p></o:p></span><=
/p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shape id=3D"Picture_x0020_9" o:s=
pid=3D"_x0000_s1026"
 type=3D"#_x0000_t75" style=3D'position:absolute;margin-left:62.8pt;margin-=
top:0;
 width:114pt;height:89.2pt;z-index:251658240;visibility:visible;
